  "summary": "zod-pino444 exfiltrates installer data via Discord relay and Hugging Face endpoints at install time",
  "details": "The package name mimics the widely-used zod/pino ecosystem but the shipped code implements a credential-harvesting and exfiltration pipeline. scripts/postinstall-agent.mjs runs as a postinstall lifecycle hook, performing host reconnaissance (ping/GET/id) and staging further code. dist/discordRelayUpload.js contains hardcoded POST endpoints and base64-encoded payloads used to relay collected data to a Discord webhook. dist/secretScan/agentStartupAudit.js and dist/secretScan/contentScanner.js scan for secrets and POST results to hardcoded huggingface.co endpoints (agent startup audit fetches to huggingface.co on lines 490/508/563). dist/hfCredentials.js decodes embedded base64 credentials used for the outbound relay, and dist/relayServer.js binds a persistent relay service. dist/deploymentDefaults.js and scripts/encode-deployment.mjs encode/embed deployment configuration as base64 blobs to obscure the destinations. Installing this package causes credential/secret collection and exfiltration to attacker-controlled Discord and Hugging Face destinations on the installer machine.",
